Script,SpiralRaiseRevisited
window.currentPBSScenario = 'SpiralRaiseRevisited';
window.currentPBSScenarioFilename = 'Spiral_Raise_Revisited';
console.log('PBS: Logging scenario selection for SpiralRaiseRevisited');
fetch('https://bba.harmonicsystems.com/api/scenario/select', {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: {
        'Content-Type': 'application/json',
        'X-Client-Version': '1.0.0'
    },
    body: JSON.stringify({
        scenario: 'SpiralRaiseRevisited',
        user: whoAmI() || 'anonymous'
    })
}).then(function(r){ console.log('PBS: Server response', r.status); }).catch(function(e){ console.log('PBS: Fetch error', e); });
setDealerCode(`

/*
convention-card-ns: 21GF-DEFAULT
convention-card-ew: 21GF-GIB
auction-filter: ((1[CD] +Pass +1H +Pass\n2H +Pass +[23])|(1[CD] +Pass +1S +Pass\n2S +Pass +[23]))
*/
produce 1000

# Spiral Raise Revisited --------------------------------------------
# South opens a minor and raises North's major to 2M on 3- or 4-card
# support.  North asks with the cheapest step (2!S over 1!H, 2N over
# 1!S) and opener spirals out support length, strength, and shortness.
# Unlike the two earlier Spiral Raise scenarios, opener may be short
# in a major or hold a 5-4-2-2, so the whole step-response ladder
# (the splinter and 5-4-2-2 answers included) can come up.

# South: 12-14 with no 5-card major, so it opens a minor (not 1M/1NT).
noFiveCardMajor = spades(south)<5 and hearts(south)<5
minorOpening = hcp(south)>11 and hcp(south)<15 and noFiveCardMajor

# North: invitational, a 4-card major, nothing longer.  Responds 1H
# with 4 hearts (4-4 goes up the line), else 1S with 4 spades.
northResponds = shape(north, 44xx+43xx+34xx -any 5xxx -any 6xxx) and hcp(north)>10 and hcp(north)<14
northBidsHearts = hearts(north)==4
northBidsSpades = spades(north)==4 and hearts(north)==3

# Opener raises North's actual major on 3- or 4-card support.
raisesHearts = northBidsHearts and hearts(south)>2 and hearts(south)<5
raisesSpades = northBidsSpades and spades(south)>2 and spades(south)<5
openerRaises = raisesHearts or raisesSpades

##### Imported Script: Define Calm Opponents #####

# Avoid concentration of values
cce = top4(east,clubs)<2
cde = top4(east,diamonds)<2
che = top4(east,hearts)<2
cse = top4(east,spades)<2
noConEast = cce and cde and che and cse

ccw = top4(west,clubs)<2
cdw = top4(west,diamonds)<2
chw = top4(west,hearts)<2
csw = top4(west,spades)<2
noConWest = ccw and cdw and chw and csw

balEast    = shape(east,any 4432 +any 4333)
unbalEast  = shape(east,xxxx -any 4432 -any 4333 -any 9xxx -any 8xxx -any 7xxx-any 6xxx -any 55xx)

balWest    = shape(west,any 4432 +any 4333)
unbalWest  = shape(west,xxxx -any 4432 -any 4333 -any 9xxx -any 8xxx -any 7xxx-any 6xxx -any 55xx)

calmEast = (unbalEast and noConEast and hcp(east)<8) or (balEast and hcp(east)<11)
calmWest = (unbalWest and noConWest and hcp(west)<8) or (balWest and hcp(west)<11)
calmOpps = calmEast and calmWest

##### End of Imported Script: Define Calm Opponents #####

# Now do it...
minorOpening and northResponds and openerRaises and calmOpps
action printoneline,
`, "S", true)
Script
Button,Spiral Raise Revisited,\n\
--- Spiral Raise Revisited\n\
Opener may raise responder's major to 2M on 3- OR 4-card support.\n\
Responder then asks with the cheapest step，and opener spirals out\n\
support length，strength，and shortness.\n\
(Weinstein: 1m 1M now what?  Wolpert: Spiral Raises.)\n\
\n\
After 1!D 1!H 2!H，responder asks with 2!S.  Opener answers:\n\
• 2N  3-card support，balanced，minimum\n\
• 3!C 4-card support，balanced\n\
• 3!D 3-card support，short in the other minor (!C)\n\
• 3!H 3-card support，short in the other major (!S)\n\
• 3!S 4-card support，splinter in !S\n\
• 3N  3-card support，balanced，maximum\n\
• 4!C 4-card support，splinter in the other minor (!C)\n\
• 4!D 5-4-2-2，maximum\n\
• 4!H 5-4-2-2，minimum\n\
(5-4-2-2 means five in the opened minor with four-card support.)\n\
\n\
After 1m 1!S 2!S the ask is 2N，the same scheme shifted up a step.\n\
A 1!C opening mirrors 1!D with the minors swapped.\n\
\n\
https://bridgewinners.com/article/view/spiral-raises/\n\
https://bridgewinners.com/article/view/1m-1m-now-what/\n\
%SpiralRaiseRevisited%,backgroundColor=lightpink
